<h1 class="hero-h">Fitness operator <em style="font-family:'Instrument Serif',serif;font-style:italic;color:#00C853;">AI buyers guide.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">The 2026 buyers guide for fitness operators evaluating AI agents and AI-native gym software. 12 evaluation criteria, the vendor questions to ask, the red flags to watch for, the contract terms to negotiate, and a scoring rubric you can fill in across the vendors you're shortlisting.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="disclosure" style="max-width:880px;margin:1rem auto;">
<strong>Disclosure:</strong> Treetop Growth Strategy is the marketing arm of Fitagentic.ai's parent company. The criteria below are the criteria we'd want a prospect to use even if it cost us the deal — because operators who pick on the right criteria stay customers, and operators who pick on the wrong ones churn within a year.
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<span class="lbl">Before you start</span>
<h2 class="h2">The honest precondition</h2>
<p class="body">If you can't articulate the specific operational bottleneck you're trying to solve — lead response speed, retention, labor cost, member experience — don't buy AI agents yet. Vendors will sell you on capability; you should buy on outcome.</p>
<p class="body">Write down the answer to this question before any vendor call: <strong>"In 12 months, what specific operational metric will be measurably better, and by how much?"</strong> If you can't fill that blank, no AI agent platform will fix it.</p>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<span class="lbl">The 12 criteria</span>
<h2 class="h2">What to evaluate (and how to weight it)</h2>

<div class="criteria-card"><h3 class="h3"><span class="criteria-num">01</span>Lead response speed (high weight)</h3>
<p style="color:#C0D8C0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Sub-60-second response with a real conversation, not just an auto-reply confirmation. <strong>Ask:</strong> "Show me the actual first-message-to-second-message cadence on a real prospect conversation."</p>
</div>

<div class="criteria-card"><h3 class="h3"><span class="criteria-num">02</span>Multi-turn conversation quality (high weight)</h3>
<p style="color:#C0D8C0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Can the agent handle a 4-6 turn conversation that veers off-script? <strong>Ask:</strong> "Let me try to break it with three off-topic questions during the demo." A vendor unwilling to let you stress-test this is a red flag.</p>
</div>

<div class="criteria-card"><h3 class="h3"><span class="criteria-num">03</span>CRM integration depth (high weight)</h3>
<p style="color:#C0D8C0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Bidirectional with your existing CRM, or only one-way? <strong>Ask:</strong> "Walk me through what data flows back to MindBody/Glofox/Zen Planner from the AI agent and on what cadence."</p>
</div>

<div class="criteria-card"><h3 class="h3"><span class="criteria-num">04</span>No-show recovery workflow (high weight)</h3>
<p style="color:#C0D8C0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Is this a default workflow or a custom-build? <strong>Ask:</strong> "What's the typical no-show recovery rate across your customer base? Show me the conversation pattern."</p>
</div>

<div class="criteria-card"><h3 class="h3"><span class="criteria-num">05</span>Member retention agent capability (medium-high weight)</h3>
<p style="color:#C0D8C0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Proactive outreach to at-risk members, or just reporting? <strong>Ask:</strong> "What churn signal triggers automatic outreach? Show me one."</p>
</div>

<div class="criteria-card"><h3 class="h3"><span class="criteria-num">06</span>SMS + voice + email channel coverage (medium weight)</h3>
<p style="color:#C0D8C0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">SMS is the highest-conversion channel for gym lead nurture in 2026. <strong>Ask:</strong> "Is SMS native or via integration? What's the deliverability rate?"</p>
</div>

<div class="criteria-card"><h3 class="h3"><span class="criteria-num">07</span>Operator visibility + override (medium-high weight)</h3>
<p style="color:#C0D8C0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Can your staff see live conversations and jump in? <strong>Ask:</strong> "Show me the operator console while an AI conversation is active."</p>
</div>

<div class="criteria-card"><h3 class="h3"><span class="criteria-num">08</span>Brand voice + customization (medium weight)</h3>
<p style="color:#C0D8C0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Can the agent's voice match your studio's vibe? <strong>Ask:</strong> "Show me three customer instances with materially different brand voices."</p>
</div>

<div class="criteria-card"><h3 class="h3"><span class="criteria-num">09</span>Reporting + ROI attribution (medium weight)</h3>
<p style="color:#C0D8C0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Can you attribute revenue back to the agent's interventions? <strong>Ask:</strong> "Show me a customer dashboard with revenue attribution. Don't just tell me you have one."</p>
</div>

<div class="criteria-card"><h3 class="h3"><span class="criteria-num">10</span>Time to value (medium weight)</h3>
<p style="color:#C0D8C0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Days to first live conversation? <strong>Ask:</strong> "What does a real onboarding timeline look like for an operator like me?" If they say "depends," push for a specific number.</p>
</div>

<div class="criteria-card"><h3 class="h3"><span class="criteria-num">11</span>Pricing model (medium weight)</h3>
<p style="color:#C0D8C0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Flat platform fee, per-conversation, per-location, per-active-member? Each has different incentives. <strong>Ask:</strong> "Model my pricing at 2x my current member base — what does it look like?"</p>
</div>

<div class="criteria-card"><h3 class="h3"><span class="criteria-num">12</span>Contract flexibility (medium weight)</h3>
<p style="color:#C0D8C0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Annual lock-in vs month-to-month? Termination terms? <strong>Ask:</strong> "What's your shortest available commitment? What's the cancellation process?"</p>
</div>

</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<span class="lbl">Red flags</span>
<h2 class="h2">Walk away if you see these</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Vendor refuses to let you stress-test the conversation during the demo.</strong> They're hiding fragility.</li>
<li><strong>Pricing requires you to commit annually before you see a working agent on your data.</strong> Real platforms run a 14-30 day pilot.</li>
<li><strong>No published customer logos or case studies with measurable outcomes.</strong> Ask for two reference calls; a real vendor has them ready.</li>
<li><strong>"AI features" that are actually template marketing automation with an LLM wrapped around it.</strong> Ask the multi-turn off-script question — you'll know in 30 seconds.</li>
<li><strong>Pricing model that punishes you for growth.</strong> Per-conversation pricing without a cap creates incentive misalignment.</li>
<li><strong>No data-portability story.</strong> If you can't export your member data and conversation history at any time, you're trapped.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<span class="lbl">Contract terms to negotiate</span>
<h2 class="h2">What to push on</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Month-to-month for the first 90 days,</strong> then annual after success criteria are met.</li>
<li><strong>Defined success criteria</strong> in writing — "lead response time under 60 seconds, no-show recovery rate at 20%+, deployed at all locations" — with a free-exit clause if not met.</li>
<li><strong>Pricing cap</strong> on per-conversation or per-active-member tiers — protect against accidental cost explosion during a viral marketing moment.</li>
<li><strong>Data export rights</strong> on demand, in a structured format (JSON, CSV).</li>
<li><strong>Implementation included</strong> for the first 30 days — no separate professional services fee.</li>
<li><strong>Quarterly business reviews</strong> with the vendor's success team, with documented KPI tracking.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

